<article class="node-32 node node-blog node-promoted node-teaser clearfix" about="/blog/marketing-better-world" typeof="sioc:Post sioct:BlogPost">

      <header>
                    <h2 class="node__title node-title"><a href="../blog/marketing-better-world">Marketing for a Better World</a></h2>
            <span property="dc:title" content="Marketing for a Better World" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
                  <span class="user-picture">
    <div class="image-and-caption"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="../sites/default/files/styles/portrait/public/pictures/picture-2-1449696235.jpg?itok=8SYkzVKE" width="100" height="128" alt="Tim Mack" title="Tim Mack" /><div class="caption-holder" style="width:100px; max-width:100% !important;"><p class="image-caption">Tim Mack</p></div></div>  </span>
        <p class="submitted">
          <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2015-04-13T21:56:43-04:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Submitted by <span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/tim-mack" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype="">Tim Mack</span> on <time pubdate datetime="2015-04-13T21:56:43-04:00">Mon, 2015-04-13 21:56</time></span>        </p>
      
          </header>
  
  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>While I have written in the past about the revolution that the world of retail is undergoing, one interesting thing about the future is that it keeps unfolding. Like any lively crossroads of converging technologies, the principles of retail choice (or should I say persuasion) brings psychology, behavioral economics, and even neuroscience together with digital technology to change the mechanics of human decision making.</p></div></div></div>
  <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="../blog/marketing-better-world" rel="tag" title="Marketing for a Better World">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Marketing for a Better World</span></a></li>
</ul>
  
</article>
<article class="node-30 node node-blog node-promoted node-teaser clearfix" about="/blog/nanotech-and-cancer" typeof="sioc:Post sioct:BlogPost">

      <header>
                    <h2 class="node__title node-title"><a href="https://www.aaiforesight.com/blog/nanotech-and-cancer"> Nanotech and Cancer</a></h2>
            <span property="dc:title" content=" Nanotech and Cancer" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
                  <span class="user-picture">
    <div class="image-and-caption"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="../sites/default/files/styles/portrait/public/pictures/picture-2-1449696235.jpg?itok=8SYkzVKE" width="100" height="128" alt="Tim Mack" title="Tim Mack" /><div class="caption-holder" style="width:100px; max-width:100% !important;"><p class="image-caption">Tim Mack</p></div></div>  </span>
        <p class="submitted">
          <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2015-03-29T23:22:52-04:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Submitted by <span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/tim-mack" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype="">Tim Mack</span> on <time pubdate datetime="2015-03-29T23:22:52-04:00">Sun, 2015-03-29 23:22</time></span>        </p>
      
          </header>
  
  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>One of the most encouraging trends in medicine in recent years is the growth of systemic approaches to problem solving, much like approaches in foresight. In other words, a range of factors often affect an outcome, each requiring a solution that must work effectively in combination with other related solutions.</p></div></div></div>
  <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="https://www.aaiforesight.com/blog/nanotech-and-cancer" rel="tag" title=" Nanotech and Cancer">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about  Nanotech and Cancer</span></a></li>
</ul>
  
</article>
<article class="node-28 node node-blog node-promoted node-teaser clearfix" about="/blog/jumping-technology-categories" typeof="sioc:Post sioct:BlogPost">

      <header>
                    <h2 class="node__title node-title"><a href="../blog/jumping-technology-categories">Jumping Technology Categories</a></h2>
            <span property="dc:title" content="Jumping Technology Categories" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
                  <span class="user-picture">
    <div class="image-and-caption"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="../sites/default/files/styles/portrait/public/pictures/picture-2-1449696235.jpg?itok=8SYkzVKE" width="100" height="128" alt="Tim Mack" title="Tim Mack" /><div class="caption-holder" style="width:100px; max-width:100% !important;"><p class="image-caption">Tim Mack</p></div></div>  </span>
        <p class="submitted">
          <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2015-03-08T13:24:47-04:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Submitted by <span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/tim-mack" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype="">Tim Mack</span> on <time pubdate datetime="2015-03-08T13:24:47-04:00">Sun, 2015-03-08 13:24</time></span>        </p>
      
          </header>
  
  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>Over the years, I have written concerning the unexpected consequences for companies of moving into technologies completely new to them, encouraged by their success in other, unrelated arenas. The illusion that success is a quality that travels with its recipient to new endeavors is a form of hubris that seems most endemic to areas like Silicon Valley in California.</p></div></div></div>
  <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="../blog/jumping-technology-categories" rel="tag" title="Jumping Technology Categories">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Jumping Technology Categories</span></a></li>
</ul>
  
</article>
<article class="node-26 node node-blog node-promoted node-teaser clearfix" about="/blog/battery-challenges-coming-years" typeof="sioc:Post sioct:BlogPost">

      <header>
                    <h2 class="node__title node-title"><a href="../blog/battery-challenges-coming-years"> Battery Challenges in Coming Years</a></h2>
            <span property="dc:title" content=" Battery Challenges in Coming Years" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
                  <span class="user-picture">
    <div class="image-and-caption"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="../sites/default/files/styles/portrait/public/pictures/picture-2-1449696235.jpg?itok=8SYkzVKE" width="100" height="128" alt="Tim Mack" title="Tim Mack" /><div class="caption-holder" style="width:100px; max-width:100% !important;"><p class="image-caption">Tim Mack</p></div></div>  </span>
        <p class="submitted">
          <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2015-02-26T00:05:08-05:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Submitted by <span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/tim-mack" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype="">Tim Mack</span> on <time pubdate datetime="2015-02-26T00:05:08-05:00">Thu, 2015-02-26 00:05</time></span>        </p>
      
          </header>
  
  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>Electric vehicles (EVs) continue to climb in attractiveness, with the Tesla Model S winning acceleration comparisons hands down. Their environmental advantages are clear, but the cost and recharge requirements of automobile batteries continue to stand in the path of broad market acceptance of EVs. Breakthroughs in this area are announced regularly; however, any celebrations might be followed by an “Oops!” announcement, or the “breakthrough” may gain no real momentum and just fade away quietly.</p></div></div></div>
  <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="../blog/battery-challenges-coming-years" rel="tag" title=" Battery Challenges in Coming Years">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about  Battery Challenges in Coming Years</span></a></li>
</ul>
  
</article>
<article class="node-24 node node-blog node-promoted node-teaser clearfix" about="/blog/solar-power-industry-and-its-growing-pains" typeof="sioc:Post sioct:BlogPost">

      <header>
                    <h2 class="node__title node-title"><a href="https://www.aaiforesight.com/blog/solar-power-industry-and-its-growing-pains"> The Solar Power Industry and Its Growing Pains</a></h2>
            <span property="dc:title" content=" The Solar Power Industry and Its Growing Pains" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
                  <span class="user-picture">
    <div class="image-and-caption"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="../sites/default/files/styles/portrait/public/pictures/picture-2-1449696235.jpg?itok=8SYkzVKE" width="100" height="128" alt="Tim Mack" title="Tim Mack" /><div class="caption-holder" style="width:100px; max-width:100% !important;"><p class="image-caption">Tim Mack</p></div></div>  </span>
        <p class="submitted">
          <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2015-02-08T12:04:38-05:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Submitted by <span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/tim-mack" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype="">Tim Mack</span> on <time pubdate datetime="2015-02-08T12:04:38-05:00">Sun, 2015-02-08 12:04</time></span>        </p>
      
          </header>
  
  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>The <a href="http://www.kiuc.coop/">Kauai Island Utility Cooperative</a> in the Hawaiian Islands would seem to be the poster child for the increasing market penetration of solar power. KIUC has quintupled utility-scale solar capacity over the past year and soon may approach 80% of peak power generation for solar on the island, as <i>MIT Technology Review</i> contributing editor <strong>Peter Fairley</strong> recently <a href="http://www.technologyreview.com/news/534266/hawaiis-solar--push-strains-the-grad">reported</a>.</p></div></div></div>
  <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="https://www.aaiforesight.com/blog/solar-power-industry-and-its-growing-pains" rel="tag" title=" The Solar Power Industry and Its Growing Pains">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about  The Solar Power Industry and Its Growing Pains</span></a></li>
</ul>
  
</article>
<article class="node-22 node node-blog node-promoted node-teaser clearfix" about="/blog/legal-nightmares-self-driving-cars" typeof="sioc:Post sioct:BlogPost">

      <header>
                    <h2 class="node__title node-title"><a href="../blog/legal-nightmares-self-driving-cars"> The Legal Nightmares of Self-Driving Cars</a></h2>
            <span property="dc:title" content=" The Legal Nightmares of Self-Driving Cars" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
                  <span class="user-picture">
    <div class="image-and-caption"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="../sites/default/files/styles/portrait/public/pictures/picture-2-1449696235.jpg?itok=8SYkzVKE" width="100" height="128" alt="Tim Mack" title="Tim Mack" /><div class="caption-holder" style="width:100px; max-width:100% !important;"><p class="image-caption">Tim Mack</p></div></div>  </span>
        <p class="submitted">
          <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2015-01-24T16:51:16-05:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Submitted by <span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/tim-mack" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype="">Tim Mack</span> on <time pubdate datetime="2015-01-24T16:51:16-05:00">Sat, 2015-01-24 16:51</time></span>        </p>
      
          </header>
  
  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>The auto industry is clearly convinced that the question of autonomous vehicles is “not if, but when,” <a href="http://blogs.motortrend.com/1501_lawyering_up_for_autonomy_technologue.html">writes <i>Motor Trend</i></a> technical director <a href="http://www.motortrend.com/staff/frank_markus/">Frank Markus</a>, reporting from a forum on Intelligent Transportation Systems in Detroit. Lux Research projects $87 billion in revenues by 2030. But the view is not so clear concerning how the longstanding legal guidelines around automotive liability will be affected.</p></div></div></div>
  <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="../blog/legal-nightmares-self-driving-cars" rel="tag" title=" The Legal Nightmares of Self-Driving Cars">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about  The Legal Nightmares of Self-Driving Cars</span></a></li>
</ul>
  
</article>
